				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 39 BARD<a name="3263"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 16 03 3:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Swarm kiting involves using your 39 charm song, selos and your two dots at the time, Fufil's and Chant of Flame.  In short (there are extensive swarm kiting posts and guides here) you proximity aggro (don't hit them) 4+++ mobs, charm one, have it attack the others, break with invis at 20% health or so, and run around being chased by the pack chant kiting the former pet til dead. Pick a new pet, have it attack the same mob you had your old pet attack and repeat. Hopefully the last mob is down to below 50% so the final chant kite isn't too tedious. If he's too healthy, I just grab another and keep going until it's a quick final kill.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps. There are better, more extensive posts, but those are the basics.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
